%% MLflow Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as User/Client
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant MLflow as MLflow Server<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS (service-ca)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3-compatible Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    Note over Client,PG: Flow 1: User Access via Gateway API

    Client->>Gateway: GET/POST /mlflow/api/*<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (Kubernetes)
    Gateway->>MLflow: Forward to 8443/TCP<br/>TLS (service-ca)<br/>URL rewrite: /mlflow/api/* -> /api/*
    MLflow->>K8sAPI: SelfSubjectAccessReview<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token<br/>Check mlflow.kubeflow.org RBAC
    K8sAPI-->>MLflow: Allowed/Denied
    MLflow->>PG: Query/Store metadata<br/>Auth: Connection string credentials<br/>TLS (configurable PGSSLMODE)
    MLflow->>S3: Store/Retrieve artifacts<br/>Auth: AWS credentials (AccessKey/SecretKey)
    S3-->>MLflow: Artifact data
    PG-->>MLflow: Metadata result
    MLflow-->>Gateway: JSON Response
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS Response

    Note over Client,PG: Flow 2: Operator Reconciliation

    participant Operator as MLflow Operator<br/>controller-manager

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch MLflow CRs<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: MLflow CR event
    Operator->>Operator: Render Helm chart<br/>CR spec -> Helm values -> K8s resources
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Server-Side Apply (SSA)<br/>Deployments, Services, HTTPRoutes,<br/>NetworkPolicies, RBAC, ConsoleLinks
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Apply result

    Note over Client,PG: Flow 3: Prometheus Metrics Scraping

    participant Prom as Prometheus

    Prom->>MLflow: GET /metrics<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS (service-ca verified)<br/>Auth: None (ServiceMonitor)
    MLflow-->>Prom: Metrics response
